sentences: At age 23, Bazin's cantata Loyse de Monfort won the 1840 Prix de Rome.
Le Trompette de Monsieur le Prince (Joubert and Melesville), 1846
La Nuit de la Saint-Sylvestre (Mélesville and M. Masson), 1849
Le Voyage en Chine (Labiche and Delacour), 1865
L'Ours et le pacha (Scribe and Saintine/J. X. Boniface), 1870
Le Voyage en Chine, which premiered at the Opéra-Comique in Paris, is his best-known composition, and continued to be staged well into the 20th century.

sentences: François Emmanuel Joseph Bazin (pronounced [fʁɑ̃.swa ba.zɛ̃]) (4 September 1816 – 2 July 1878) was a well-known French opera composer during the nineteenth century.
Although his many light operas were popular during his lifetime, they are rarely staged today.
